add(V) - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Adds the specified value (i.e., object) to this OrderedSet if it is not already present, and orders the value via the composite-key stipulated by the keyComponentProfiles of the set.

I

iterator() - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Invokes this collection's inherited HashSet iterator functionality; when the Iterator#remove method is invoked, the specified object is removed, along with any corresponding composite-key entries.

K

KeyComponentProfile<V> - Class in org.commonvox.collections
An array of KeyComponentProfile objects specifies the composite-key structure which orders the elements in an OrderedSet.
KeyComponentProfile(Class<V>, Class<K>, Method...) - Constructor for class org.commonvox.collections.KeyComponentProfile
Constructs a KeyComponentProfile belonging to an OrderedSet containing elements of class valueClass; the ordering maintained by a KeyComponentProfile is stipulated by the keyComponentClass parameter, which must either be the same as the valueClass or must correspond to a class of objects returned by one or more of the valueClass's parameterless "get" methods; submission of methodsReturningKeyComponents vararg parameters is optional.
KeyComponentProfile(Class<V>, Class<K>, Comparator<? super K>, Method...) - Constructor for class org.commonvox.collections.KeyComponentProfile
Constructs a KeyComponentProfile belonging to an OrderedSet containing elements of class valueClass; the ordering maintained by a KeyComponentProfile is stipulated by the keyComponentClass parameter, which must either be the same as the valueClass or must correspond to a class of objects returned by one or more of the valueClass's parameterless "get" methods; submission of methodsReturningKeyComponents vararg parameters is optional.
keyComponentSet(KeyComponentProfile<V>) - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Returns a Set view of all keyComponentClass-objects related to the submitted KeyComponentProfile.

O

OrderedSet<V> - Class in org.commonvox.collections
An OrderedSet provides composite-key based ordering of a set of values (analogous to composite key ordering in a relational database).
OrderedSet(KeyComponentProfile<V>...) - Constructor for class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Constructs an empty OrderedSet configured for composite-key based ordering of its values as specified in the submitted vararg array of KeyComponentProfile parameters.
OrderedSet(Collection<? extends V>, KeyComponentProfile<V>...) - Constructor for class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Constructs an OrderedSet containing the values in the specified collection, with the values ordered according to the composite-key specified in the submitted vararg array of KeyComponentProfile parameters.
org.commonvox.collections - package org.commonvox.collections
The org.commonvox.collections package currently consists of a single Collection implementation: OrderedSet (for which usage examples can be found here).

R

remove(Object) - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Removes the specified object from this set if it is present, and clears any corresponding composite-key entries.
removeAll(Collection<?>) - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet

V

values() - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Returns a List of the values contained in this OrderedSet, ordered according to composite-key structures stipulated by the array of KeyComponentProfiles with which the OrderedSet was constructed.
values(boolean) - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Returns a List of the values contained in this OrderedSet, ordered according to composite-key structures stipulated by the array of KeyComponentProfiles with which the OrderedSet was constructed; if the suppressConsecutiveDuplicates parameter is true, then any consecutive duplicate objects in the List will be suppressed.
values(Object) - Method in class org.commonvox.collections.OrderedSet
Returns a List of the values contained in this OrderedSet which share the submitted keyComponent-object as a common attribute; the submitted keyComponent-object must be of class equal to the keyComponentClass stipulated in the first KeyComponentProfile submitted to the constructor of this OrderedSet.
